The paper discusses recent work in inductive logic programming (ILP), which is a subfield of machine learning that focuses on inducing logic programs from data. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of answer set programming, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The focus on interpretability and the use of background knowledge suggest that the paper could also be classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
